A C O N C U R R E N T R E S O L U T I O N
To recognize the 250th anniversary of the United States 1
Marine Corps. 2
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
OHIO (THE SENATE CONCURRING):
WHEREAS, The United States Marine Corps was established on 3
November 10, 1775, in Tun Tavern, Philadelphia; and 4
WHEREAS, Since its founding, the United States Marine Corps 5
has earned a distinguished reputation as one of the world's 6
premier naval infantry forces, with a legacy built on an 7
unwavering fighting spirit and strict adherence to the highest 8
standards; and 9
WHEREAS, Marines pride themselves on exemplifying its motto 10
of "Semper Fidelis" or "Always Faithful"; and 11
WHEREAS, Marines have played a pivotal role in shaping the 12

